description.narrative:
The Strategic Sector Cooperation on Food aims to strengthen animal health, food safety, and public health including through improving the preparedness of the veterinary services in the handling of exotic diseases in Mexico through:

-Strengthened surveillance, improved capacity to develop and maintain contingency plans, improved diagnosis and handling of outbreaks;
-Sustainable and responsible use of veterinary medicine, including antibiotics including a first draft of a national plan to combat AMR;
-Improved traceability systems, updated meat and hygiene provisions, and strengthened monitoring of toxic contaminants.
